    },
    {
      "id": "5cf88b08c64a4148ab1d3d91b71b7a5e0bff3bec",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-24 14:00:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nBuild with \"--enable-ext4\" option:\nhttp://newbuild.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/629/",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "25ce4aaff5e23bd9281d15bd5819afa413751c9a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-24 14:27:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Verified\n\nLustre build:\nhttp://newbuild.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/629/arch=x86_64,build_type=server,distro=el5,ib_stack=inkernel/\n\nMounting the 24TB LUN with \"force_over_24tb\" mount option:\nhttps://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/2eb95a9e-8611-11e0-b4df-52540025f9af",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "c2dd49013c7f671568fec76d09271c78d6b88b05",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-24 14:43:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, approved\n\nThe only question about the patch testing is whether the patch allows mounting a filesystem of just below 24TB without any extra mount options?  It looks like it should be OK.\n\nThe other question is whether this should allow filesystems exactly equal to 24TiB in size?  We did test that worked OK, though for real \"3TB\" disks they will always be slightly smaller than 3TiB, so an 8+2 RAID-6 LUN will also be smaller than a full 24TiB in size and it probably doesn't matter. \n\nApproving this as-is, so that we can land it sooner. None of these issues are blockers.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "c60a719de38551cc24295307d05497aa2a50dc15",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 7,
        "name": "Johann Lombardi",
        "email": "johann.lombardi@intel.com",
        "username": "johann",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-05-24 20:58:28.000000000",
      "message": "Change has been successfully cherry-picked as bd5a07010489666d7adf79c074f2dbd694f49f4a.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "49f7014f1dff31f8ee8b6e8c8de0009d69c2b297",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-25 02:18:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n{quote}\nThe only question about the patch testing is whether the patch allows mounting a filesystem of just below 24TB without any extra mount options? It looks like it should be OK.\n{quote}\n\nYes, I've tested this on a 23TB LUN without any extra mount options: https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/1c2a154e-8675-11e0-b4df-52540025f9af\n\n{quote}\nThe other question is whether this should allow filesystems exactly equal to 24TiB in size? We did test that worked OK, though for real \"3TB\" disks they will always be slightly smaller than 3TiB, so an 8+2 RAID-6 LUN will also be smaller than a full 24TiB in size and it probably doesn't matter.\n{quote}\n\n+       if (ext4_blocks_count(es) >= (6ULL << 30)) {\n+               if (force_over_24tb == 0) {\n+                       printk(KERN_ERR \"EXT4-fs does not support filesystems \"\n+                              \"greater than 24TB and can cause data corruption.\"\n+                              \"Use \\\"force_over_24tb\\\" mount option to override.\"\n+                              \"\\n\");\n+                       goto failed_mount;\n+               }\n+       }\n\nIf the filesystem equals to 24TB in size, then \"force_over_24tb\" is also needed. Should I change the \">=\" to \">\" in the above codes?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "03dac268ee9d383df1de328d7c82be21370afa03",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-25 03:29:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> If the filesystem equals to 24TB in size, then \"force_over_24tb\" is also needed.\n> Should I change the \">=\" to \">\" in the above codes?\n\nSince this patch has already been merged I don't think any additional change is needed.  In the past we wanted to restrict filesystems to be strictly less than 2^32 blocks.  For the future it is probably better to use \"> {tested size}\" instead of \">=\" since it is likely that LVM LVs and other LUNs will have exact power-of-two sizes.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "f102b384240684a6998442ee1126aec8c2d28964",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-25 03:37:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> For the future it is probably better to use \"> {tested size}\" instead of \">=\" since it is likely that LVM LVs and other LUNs will have exact power-of-two sizes.\n\nOK, got it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    }
  ],
